%pyspark
import psycopg2
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.close()
conn = psycopg2.connect("dbname='gpadmin' user='gpadmin' host='192.168.9.154' password='gpadmin' port='10432'")
cur = conn.cursor()
cur.execute("SELECT compressionratio,price FROM auto_price limit 4")
rows = cur.fetchall()
cr = []
pr = []
for row in rows:
    cr.append(float(row[0]))
    pr.append(float(row[1]))
print (cr)
print (pr)

plt.scatter(cr,pr)

show(plt)
